1
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:05,040
I hope you won't forget to talk
to your mom about Saturday, okay?

2
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,600
Otherwise, it’ll cost a lot of money.

3
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:08,960
For sure, for sure, a lot of money.
-Yeah.

4
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:10,840
Remind me what’s happening on Saturday.

5
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:14,000
Oh, you forgot already? The girl's ballet performance.

6
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:16,280
No, no, I didn’t forget, why would I forget?

7
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:19,000
Is it happening on Saturday?
-Yeah.

8
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,240
Okay, okay, okay.

9
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,360
Time flies.
-Crazy.

10
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:25,680
Look at that, in two weeks,
basically, 14 days have passed, amazing.

11
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,800
And the babysitter?
-She can’t, she has exams.

12
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,680
And my mom is taking my dad for tests.

13
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,720
So you won’t forget?
-Forget what?

14
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,320
To talk to your mom about the ballet?

15
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:38,000
Maybe we should let my mom rest?

16
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,160
Why? Why always let your mom rest?

17
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:43,160
She herself says
she’ll only rest in the grave, God willing,

18
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:45,040
So until that happens, at least let her help us.

19
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,440
I really think it’s a bad idea
to ask my mom.

20
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:50,000
Wow, come on, aren’t you tired of yourself?

21
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:52,040
Seriously, aren’t you tired of yourself

22
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:54,120
that you can’t stand up once
to your mom and insist?

23
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:56,040
Because everything you ask her, she says no.

24
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:59,520
When it’s something really important
then I know how to ask and insist.

25
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:02,120
Yeah? So here, now you need
to insist, don’t you get it?

26
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:05,000
Let’s see you be a man, standing
in front of your mom face-to-face

27
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,040
not like some Arab baboon.

28
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,640
Look at me, look at me and...

29
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:30,080
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, with my respect.

30
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,000
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Dad.

31
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:32,000
Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat.

32
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,680
How are you?
-What’s up?

33
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,200
Shai’s whining is coming soon.

34
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:39,080
You have a mission, right?
-No whining will happen.

35
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,040
Is Shai about to whine?
-A little.

36
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:45,000
He needs to go talk to Riki about Saturday.

37
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:48,320
What’s happening on Saturday?
-We have the big ballet performance

38
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,800
and I have no one to leave the little one with.

39
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:52,560
You want Riki to babysit.
-Yeah, I know,

40
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:55,240
I thought if it works out,
I don’t know, maybe she’ll agree.

41
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,280
You made me laugh. Since when does Riki agree to anything?

42
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:03,760
If it accidentally slips out of her mouth,
I immediately know she’s not feeling well.

43
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:06,560
That’s what annoys me, Pinchas,
you know how annoying that is?

44
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:08,000
I hear all my friends talking

45
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,400
about how grandmas run around the house yelling "take the grandkids."

46
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:13,400
And Riki, as you say, is a mess.

47
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:16,200
Oh, Riki is a mess,
that was her name before she got married.

48
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:21,160
Shabbat, you’re putting Shai in a deadly minefield

49
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,640
that no one has returned from with a yes.

50
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:24,920
Have mercy on him.

51
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,360
Where is she? Why isn’t she coming to say hello?

52
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,120
Shabbat’s in the living room, she’s saying hello to Dad.

53
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,920
Take it easy, Mom.
-I’m completely calm.

54
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,560
Are there any leftovers from the schnitzel butchers?

55
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:38,320
What happened? You can tell me, I’m your mom.

56
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:41,520
What’s wrong? Did she do something to you?

57
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:45,480
Do you need legal advice? Help?
-Help, yes.

58
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,560
Here it goes.

59
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:51,800
Mom, we need you to help us watch the little one
on Saturday

60
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,840
because the big one has a performance in ballet class.

61
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,920
Is that it? I thought something happened to you.

62
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,280
No, nothing's happened to me so far.

63
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,760
So why didn’t you just say it when you got here?

64
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,240
Why did you have to beat around the bush?

65
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:06,800
You know me, I like it
when people are straightforward.

66
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:10,000
So is that okay with you?
-How did you come to that conclusion?

67
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:13,520
If you were an only child, maybe that would be less likely.

68
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:17,000
But as you know, you’re not an only child
and if I agree to babysit for you,

69
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,800
your siblings will line up.

70
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:21,600
Especially Adam.
-Even one Adam is a lot.

71
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:24,320
Mom, come on,
why don’t you help out? They’re your granddaughters.

72
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:28,520
Shai, you know I love your granddaughters

73
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,280
and I have no problem with them,

74
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:34,680
but if I agree this time
Itamar will come with his kids

75
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:37,000
and ask me to babysit for him too.

76
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:42,840
His kids, let them stay with a babysitter, they’re a bit tough.

77
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,880
Not like your little angels, whom I love so much

78
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,600
and I’m ready to do anything for them.

79
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,120
So I take it you’re saying no.

80
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,880
Understanding has never been your problem.

81
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:58,080
She’s so negative
that this game of yes, no, black, white

82
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,760
for her it’s just no, black.

83
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,280
In the atoms that make her up
there are no protons or neutrons

84
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,840
just negative electrons.

85
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,400
What, Pinchas, are you telling me
she’s never said yes?

86
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,280
Maybe when I proposed to her.
-No, what, then she said yes.

87
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,440
Not exactly, I think she said:

88
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:16,440
"Well, at least there’ll be someone to bury me."

89
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:19,160
I’m just kidding, of course.
-Yeah, yeah, of course.

90
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:20,560
Shabbat Shalom.

91
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:23,840
Hey, Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

92
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:27,240
What’s this? Itamar is downstairs?

93
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,440
Why?
-Shabbat Shalom.

94
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,400
You’re not.

95
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,080
Meet Ravit.

96
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,480
My dad, Pinchas.
-Nice to meet you.

97
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:42,120
Nice to meet you, Ravit, I’m Shai.

98
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,600
You rascal.
-I...

99
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:48,760
Ravit, you look familiar to me,

100
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,520
haven’t you been here before?
-I don’t think so.

101
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,240
Awesome.

102
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,680
So Itamar isn’t here yet.

103
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,160
This isn’t an April Fool’s joke, right?
-No.

104
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,320
Unless they moved daylight saving time
six months ahead.

105
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,640
No?
-No.

106
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:13,080
Maybe... maybe this time, Mom,
just this once, you’ll agree.

107
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:17,200
Shai, I explained to you why not and it’s final.

108
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,920
But Mom, it’s really important to me.

109
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,520
I raised my kids and I raised them well,

110
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,000
now it’s your turn.

111
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:28,400
And they don’t know each other?
-No.

112
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,960
Who?

113
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,920
Ravit... Ravit?

114
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,200
Excuse me, what do you do?

115
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:37,320
I’m a lingerie model.
-Nice.

116
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:40,240
And you don’t mind the whole world seeing your underwear?

117
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,200
Not everyone thinks about nudity right away,

118
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,720
you know, underwear is like a swimsuit,
you don’t see anything.

119
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:49,520
Dad, anyone who wants to see underwear today
doesn’t need Ravit for that,

120
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,880
they just go online.

121
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,840
Do you have the address of her website?
-She doesn’t have her own site.

122
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:57,240
But you can just go
to any website and see everything there.

123
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,240
Any website?

124
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:02,360
Any dot co dot
Giorgio Armani question mark.

125
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,840
Hey, the girls are here.

126
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,360
Can you come to the balcony for a sec?
-Sure, Luli Shbaluli.

127
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,840
Sit down.
-What?

128
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,960
Wow, who’s that?
-That’s Shai, my brother.

129
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,680
No way, I can’t believe it, he looks just like my brother-in-law.

130
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,040
No, I’m dying.

131
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,240
Are you sure they don’t know each other?
-I’m sure.

132
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,200
Rascal.

133
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,200
I see you came back with your tail tucked in.

134
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:30,000
Should I guess the answer?
-No, the tail isn’t tucked.

135
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,320
I argued, I stood my ground,

136
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,760
but in the end, I considered her and gave in.

137
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:39,160
Oh, you gave in. What a noble soul,
truly a righteous among the nations.

138
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,440
I feel like planting a whole forest in your name.

139
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,880
Sorry, Shai, she gave me a logical explanation.

140
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,720
That’s why I didn’t push too hard.

141
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,680
What logical explanation did she give?

142
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,760
That she’s a misanthropic
obsessive narcissist?

143
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,560
Kind of, she just phrased it a bit differently.

144
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:53,480
You’re exactly what I
thought of you, you’re a wimp.

145
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:57,000
Wimp is too strong a word, you’re a softie.

146
00:06:57,560 --> 00:07:00,240
What are we going to do about Saturday?
-If there’s no solution, there’s no ballet.

147
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,560
And just so you know, the girl has been
working on this performance for a week.

148
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:06,560
Aren’t you exaggerating a bit?
-No, it’s either your mom or everything’s canceled.

149
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:10,680
And just know that you’re the one who’ll go and tell the girl
that because of your mom, there’s no ballet.

150
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,240
Shabbat Shalom, Dad.

151
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,120
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

152
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,400
What’s up?
-The crying of Itamar.

153
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,680
There won’t be any crying.

154
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,640
Sweetie.

155
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,120
Ohh
ohh

156
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,360
Amazing.

157
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,240
Ronit, meet Michal.

158
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:39,480
Hi, nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

159
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:43,080
That was your brother.
-That’s Itamar. Yeah, I’m his wife.

160
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,120
You look great with your hair.

161
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,560
What, this? It’s super easy, want me to show you?

162
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,240
Thanks, you’re so sweet.

163
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:52,480
It’s unbelievable, right?
-Gorgeous.

164
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,840
Shabbat Shalom, Itamar.
-Shabbat Shalom.

165
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:01,520
Did you come alone?
-No, Michal’s in the living room, she says hi.

166
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,400
Oh, then send her back.

167
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,720
And where are your cute kids?
-Scattered around.

168
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:11,680
Speaking of kids, Mom, we
need help on Tuesday night.

169
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:15,240
What’s going on with you all,
is there no babysitter in the world?

170
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,640
She’s not available, the babysitter,
I think it’s exam season,

171
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,880
and we have to go to Michal’s graduation
and we have no arrangement for the kids.

172
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,160
And Smadar?

173
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:25,160
That’s the day the kids are with me
and she won’t hear of an alternative.

174
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,800
-No.

175
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,360
Mom.

176
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,920
Wow, it’s so simple! It’s amazing.

177
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,919
I told you, you look great.
-Sweetie.

178
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,919
Hey, there you are.
-Hey, Shabbat Shalom.

179
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,080
I need to talk to you.
-Just a sec.

180
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:40,400
In private.

181
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:45,160
Shai, come here.
-Sure.

182
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,600
Hey.
-What's going on here?

183
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,560
Amazing, right?

184
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,720
Ravit, meet: Shai, my brother.
-Wow, no way, this is unbelievable.

185
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:59,560
Did you see the resemblance too?
-What do you mean, did I see?

186
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,760
You look just like my brother-in-law, like two peas in a pod.

187
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,280
He might be a bit taller
and has brown eyes,

188
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,360
but seriously, it's spot on.
-Same voice.

189
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,240
Wow, I'm dying.

190
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,680
Did Itamar see this?

191
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,640
-Not yet.

192
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,560
Where is he?
-Tell him to come.

193
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,320
Little rascal.

194
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,800
But why, Mom, why?

195
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,720
Itamar, when I was a young mom
no one helped me.

196
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:27,160
But what can we do if times have changed?
Nowadays, parents help their kids.

197
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:30,200
My dear, if I help you
and babysit for you,

198
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:34,000
your siblings will line up here.
-I don't get you, Mom, really,

199
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,440
they're your grandkids.

200
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:41,840
Itamar, you know I love
my grandkids and I have no problem with them,

201
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:46,080
but if I agree this time,
Shai will come with his kids

202
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,160
and ask me to babysit for them too.

203
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:53,320
And let's keep this between us, his kids are a bit tough,

204
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:59,640
not like your angels that I adore
and I'm ready to do anything for them.

205
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,000
You know what I'll do, Mom,

206
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,480
I won't tell them you babysat for us.

207
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:06,800
Itamar, you know I don't like
doing favors.

208
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,480
Come on, but Mom.

209
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,480
Itamar, the door is closed.

210
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:17,520
What?
-No, I can't deal with this.

211
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,840
You're right, it's really not fair of Adam.

212
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,560
What, why? What did Adam do?
No, I wanted to talk to you about Riki.

213
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:24,360
Oh, okay.

214
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,040
Please.

215
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,560
I need you to teach me how
you raised Shai to stand up to his mom

216
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,320
and ask for things and actually get them.

217
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,760
You think I raised him?

218
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,080
He's scared of her
more than he's scared of the tax office.

219
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,640
Just now, in the car, we had an argument about it

220
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:38,160
because we need a babysitter
for Monday and she's not willing to help.

221
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,200
No way, what a coincidence.

222
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,520
We need one for Tuesday too,

223
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,280
and I sent Itamar to talk to her, maybe she'll agree.

224
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,360
The chances are zero,

225
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,920
he went, he begged her,
she completely shut him down.

226
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:47,760
Well, then we're in the same boat.

227
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,600
With Captain Riki Rosen.

228
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,760
So what can we do?
-Now, nothing,

229
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,800
we should have drowned her with the albatross.

230
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,720
Now I've lost you.

231
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:00,080
But forget it, what did Adam do wrong?

232
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,000
No, you know,

233
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:05,800
still coming every week
with a different girl, it's not...

234
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,760
In the meantime.

235
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,200
Right.

236
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:15,600
Babe, we don't have a plan for Tuesday.

237
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,800
What?
-Sorry, I turned into a nerd.

238
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,560
His mom already beat me in the first half.

239
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,360
I don't know what you're talking about.

240
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,680
You sent me to talk to my mom.

241
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,040
And you're right, she’s not willing to watch the kids.

242
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,760
She said it’s because of Shai’s childhood
but he should stay in Yavivo.

243
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:32,800
I’m Ravit, coming in hot.
-What?

244
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,160
Who?

245
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,760
I’m Ravit, Adam’s friend.
-What’s going on here?

246
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,960
Well, she said no?
-Yeah, but...

247
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,840
No, yeah, I see the resemblance.
-Really?

248
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:48,680
Did you talk to her?
-I was busy with this event.

249
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,520
Wait, wait, let me try talking to her.

250
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,840
Later, tell me what happened here.

251
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,680
No, this is unbelievable.

252
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:58,800
It’s like that game.
-Find the differences.

253
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,800
What, there’s no difference, it’s exactly the same.

254
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:04,600
Look, look, you found one, the dot.

255
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:07,040
Oh, right, she has a dot, that’s big.

256
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,440
No, you’re not normal.
-Bro, I thought it would be good

257
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,000
But not that much.

258
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,840
What?

259
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:18,000
Rivka, could you make a real effort
to help the kids a bit?

260
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,960
Maybe we can watch the grandkids, maybe...

261
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:24,640
First of all, don’t speak in plural,
just do it, help, we’ll watch,

262
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:27,600
you know very well you can’t
neither help nor watch,

263
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,400
not even your own balls’ order.

264
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:33,160
Rivka, these are our grandkids.

265
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:36,080
Pinchas, you know I love our grandkids,

266
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:39,000
but if I agree to babysit them this time,

267
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:43,360
they’ll come back in a week asking
and another week and another week.

268
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:46,160
But it’s not about another week
and another week,

269
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,320
it’s about Monday, Tuesday.
-Pinchas, Pinchas,

270
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:50,680
And what will happen when we’re out of energy?

271
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:53,920
What will happen in a few weeks
when we can’t anymore? What then?

272
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:59,120
Adam will come with his kids and say,
why aren’t you babysitting me?

273
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:03,040
What will happen then? Pinchas, I’m thinking about our future

274
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,480
and theirs.

275
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:09,640
They need to learn to manage on their own.
-Okay, okay.

276
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,920
Wait, what are you talking about?
-About the resemblance.

277
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,320
Yeah, but which one?

278
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,680
Between Shai and Itamar regarding their mom.

279
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:20,600
What a coincidence, I was talking
about the resemblance between Shai and Gihan.

280
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,120
Oh, so we’re not even talking about the same thing?

281
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,800
No, what a coincidence.
-No, what a coincidence.

282
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,720
No, I’m dying.
-No, I’m dying.

283
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,080
No, this is a YouTube moment.

284
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:32,960
No, my sister-in-law, I’m one step ahead of you.

285
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:37,240
If I insist a bit more, will it help?

286
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,760
It won’t help, right?

287
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:43,280
Pinchas.
-Sorry, I was just trying to insist.

288
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,120
Since when did you become stubborn?

289
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,040
Go call everyone to eat,

290
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:50,600
I just want to finish this and run away.
-Okay.

291
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,080
Friends are requested in the dining room.
-In a bit, we’re not hungry.

292
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,240
Speak for yourself, I’m hungry.
-What’s new?

293
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:01,600
Tell me, babe, are you by any chance vegetarian?
-Yeah. Wow, how did you know?

294
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,640
Sometimes I see into people.

295
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:06,600
The outside she sometimes misses.

296
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:08,840
No, it kills me how similar you all are.

297
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:12,240
Ravitush, babe,
if there’s one small thing I’ve learned in my life,

298
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:15,360
it’s that no one likes
being told they look like someone else.

299
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,440
No one.

300
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,760
Well, I’m sorry to interrupt
this Boscilla moment here.

301
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:22,200
So, Pinchas, anything new?
-Not really, just the usual.

302
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:25,240
Pinchas, come on, are you calling them?

303
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,560
I’ll answer the phone.

304
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,000
Hello.

305
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,280
Yes, Fabiela, yes.

306
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:34,920
What are you saying?

307
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,640
So it must be really tough.

308
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,480
What, for four days? In two weeks?

309
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,480
No, no, I don’t think we...

310
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,520
It’s already time, goodbye.

311
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,200
You know what, it’s fine, we’ll take it,

312
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,040
No point in wasting it.

313
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:56,160
Thanks, Fab', here, your requests are already here.

314
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:58,720
So bye, bye, Fanny.

315
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,880
Is everyone here?
-Yeah, everyone came.

316
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:09,080
I see someone’s here twice.

317
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,960
What’s this?
-That’s Ravit.

318
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,880
This is my first time here.

319
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,600
Little rascal.
-I know you’ll love it.

320
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,960
Wow.

321
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,760
You look gorgeous!

322
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,240
Michal, you could learn from her.
-Learn what?

323
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:28,920
Okay, quiet, I have wonderful news.

324
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:33,720
Silvan had a tough surgery, it’s nonsense,

325
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:38,440
I’m inviting all of you
in two weeks for four days

326
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,880
to a suite at the "Fun Hotel,"

327
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:46,560
there are four big rooms
facing one pool and it’s all ours.

328
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:50,120
So no "I can’t," clear your schedules,

329
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,200
everyone’s coming, no exceptions.

330
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,320
Because if we don’t all come

331
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:58,960
then Fanny gives this vacation to Mel' Tavalet.

332
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,840
Ballet.

333
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,400
So is that okay?

334
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:03,960
Of course.
-Cool.

335
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:05,320
Why not?

336
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,800
Riki, it’s not that simple,

337
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:10,640
I need a second to make a call
to check if it’s okay, okay?

338
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:12,520
Ornit, call me, I’m waiting for you here.

339
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:15,000
Okay, I’m stepping out to the balcony for a sec.
Shai, come with me for a minute.

340
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:18,520
Why interrupt him in the middle of eating?
Do we need to pause for one phone call?

341
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,040
Mom, I’ll be right back.

342
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,320
Well, if we’re doing it, then let’s do it, Itamar, come with me.

343
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,720
I’m waiting for you here.

344
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:29,360
At least you’re not alone.
-And not in the dark.

345
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,000
Very funny.

346
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:34,680
Not like your friend, but it’s funny.

347
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,480
What’s funny?

348
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:40,600
So what’s Dad doing besides wandering around the country?

349
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:44,280
What?
-How cute.

350
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,320
Right?

351
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,600
Thanks.

352
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,880
What was so urgent that you had to
pull me out in the middle of eating?

353
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,280
Well, don’t confuse things, you haven’t even started eating.

354
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,120
Listen, this time I’m not ready.

355
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,880
Why? It’s a free vacation, it doesn’t cost a dime.

356
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,760
It’ll be nice to spend the weekend together,

357
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,960
it’s also great for family bonding, what’s wrong with that?

358
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:03,520
What’s wrong is that my whole body is already shaking.

359
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,040
Okay, sit down, you’re exaggerating a bit.
-Am I exaggerating or is your mom exaggerating?

360
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,319
Like every word she says
everyone has to stand at attention.

361
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,760
Why the silence?
-Why? Because you and your trained brothers...

362
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:13,520
Don’t say a word after
she says the last word.

363
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,640
Shai, I’m done with this, it’s either me or her.

364
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,160
Shani, don’t put me in an awkward position.

365
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:20,359
You’ll find a solution, Shai, just say
the dates don’t work for you,

366
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,160
Say it doesn’t fit with your study buddy.
-Shani, but...

367
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,520
You know what? Come on, I’ll make it easier for you,

368
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:27,440
If your mom helps you with ballet on Monday,

369
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,400
we’ll go with them to the "Fun Hotel."

370
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:33,560
You’re mixing things that don’t go together.
What’s the connection between ballet and the Fun Hotel?

371
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:37,800
Shai, you need to be strong now.
Stand up to her and don’t break.

372
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:40,880
Listen to me, find the connection,
I have no idea how,

373
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:45,160
if there’s ballet on Monday, there’s the Fun Hotel and vice versa.

374
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,600
I have no idea how. Make something up.

375
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,440
Fine, we’re not going to that Rikitours,

376
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,360
we’re not jumping for every one of her whims.

377
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:56,640
Shai, you don’t want to get into trouble with her,
my mom will never forgive you for this.

378
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,680
You’re on my mom’s blacklist
in the Knesset, that’s your end.

379
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:02,400
Sorry, it’s not just me, we’re in this together,
if I’m not going, then you’re not going either.

380
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:05,320
Sure, yeah, but let’s not make a big deal out of it.

381
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,000
It’s not a big deal, you just need to put
the Fun Hotel and the babysitter for Tuesday on the table.

382
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,120
There’s a babysitter, there’s the Fun Hotel, clear?
-Clear.

383
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,960
Listen, I can’t come
to that Fun Hotel, I have something.

384
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:15,640
Well, you told me you wanted
to get to know me better,

385
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:18,040
so here’s your chance
to get to know me and the whole family.

386
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:21,760
You guys have the overbearing mom syndrome,

387
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,480
if you don’t do what she wants, there’s terror.

388
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,160
What are you talking about?

389
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:26,680
So let’s see you tell her no to that Fun Hotel.

390
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:28,360
Come on, stand your ground, show me
you’re not just obeying her automatically.

391
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:31,440
Fine, you’ll see.
-Fine.

392
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:34,160
Now, now, come on, come on.

393
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,360
Mom,

394
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:41,920
look!

395
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,800
We’re not sure we can go to the Fun Hotel.
-Why?

396
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:49,760
I mean we can’t give you a positive answer yet.

397
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:53,400
Why?
-Because there’s the...

398
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,560
Babysitter on Monday
and only then we’ll give you an answer.

399
00:18:57,760 --> 00:19:02,440
I get it, you’re giving your mom an ultimatum.
-What? No way.

400
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:05,560
What ultimatum? What are you talking about?

401
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,360
There’s just a connection between the two things.

402
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:10,840
Can you please explain to me what the connection is
between the Fun Hotel and the babysitter?

403
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:13,960
There is a connection.

404
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,640
An indirect one.
-I understand.

405
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,040
Riki.
-Nice.

406
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,400
I’m glad it’s nice here because mom...

407
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,920
Check this out,

408
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:27,800
we can’t come because of the babysitter

409
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,160
and because Michal has a graduation ceremony.

410
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,800
But that’s on a completely different date.

411
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:37,320
Yeah, but...
-What are you even talking to me about?

412
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,520
No, the...

413
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,240
Honey, I can’t do this.
-I’m not feeling well.

414
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,920
Wait, can someone explain to me
what all this nonsense is?
-Adam.

415
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:47,520
No way.

416
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:48,760
We’re not coming, Ravit has a show,

417
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,280
lingerie.

418
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:52,800
לא נכון.

419
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:57,760
אנחנו לא נגיע, לרווית יש תצוגה,

420
00:19:57,840 --> 00:19:58,960
הלבשה תחתונה.

421
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:00,200
What, why are you involving me?

422
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,640
Because it’s not me, you think?

423
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:06,120
Mich... Ravit doesn’t want to come.
-I don’t care about anything,

424
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:08,600
Whoever doesn’t show up, raise your hand now.

425
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,360
The question wasn’t phrased accurately.

426
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,600
Rebellion?

427
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,560
Really, it’s not a rebellion, it’s just...

428
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,640
Those are your grandkids, right?
-I just want what’s best for them.

429
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:32,080
My cuties, what do you prefer, a ballet show

430
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:36,480
or a vacation by the pool in Eilat?

431
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,120
Girls, this isn’t up for choice.

432
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:41,000
But I just want you to know you can have both,

433
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:42,240
it’s just Grandma doesn’t want...

434
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:46,360
I’m willing to do the babysitting.
-And Avchan needs you on Tuesday.

435
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:48,200
Please, I told you. Your turn.

436
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:53,080
What about you, don’t you have any demands?
-Adam, I want to go.

437
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,600
With us to Fun Hotel?

438
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:57,320
No, now, home.

439
00:20:58,080 --> 00:20:59,040
Of course.

440
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,600
Hello.

441
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:03,880
Yes, Fabaila.

442
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:10,800
So it’s just a short surgery in the end,
so he needs the hotel for recovery.

443
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,240
What a question, as long as he’s healthy.

444
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,600
Yes.

445
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:18,360
At "Fab," that’s perfectly fine.
At "Bi," may he be healthy.

446
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:22,640
In the end, he needs the hotel for recovery.

447
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,440
And the babysitter?
-Not feeling so well.

448
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,800
Because we lost the hotel.

449
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,280
Is there a connection?
-There is a connection.

450
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,520
Indirect.

451
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:37,960
From all this mess that in the end
there’s no Fun Hotel and no babysitter.

452
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,280
So I thought, maybe you’ll take the older one to ballet

453
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:42,360
and I’ll stay home with the little one?
-There’s a babysitter.

454
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,840
Where from?
-I knew your mom wouldn’t end up doing it.

455
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,000
You arranged it with Meirav.

456
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:46,960
Yes
Meirav
yes.

457
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,440
How much is she charging for that?
-300.

458
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,640
For everything.
-Per hour.

459
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,800
And after midnight it’s double the rate.

460
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,000
I told you it would cost you a lot of money.

461
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:55,960
Of course, a lot of money.

462
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,720
But for that price, even my mom
would agree to do it.

463
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,800
No, let your mom run away,

464
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,640
just run away.

465
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:07,360
What are we doing about the day off?
-There’s no day off,

466
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:11,520
no day off, no.
-No.

467
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,600
I won’t tell them you babysat him.

468
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:17,440
Itamar, you know I don’t like
those silly tricks.

469
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,640
What are we doing about the day off?

470
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:22,400
Why are you bringing this up again? Wait.

471
